  "markdown": "![ Can I use Benchtop NMR in my lab?](https://forms.cloud.quantumsimulations.de/tmp/assets/fa068d96/HQS_Logo_colour_V01.png)\n  * [ Load unfinished survey ](https://forms.cloud.quantumsimulations.de/webinar-can-i-use-benchtop-NMR-in-my-lab)\n\n\nYou have completed 0% of this survey\n0% \nCaution: JavaScript execution is disabled in your browser or for this website. You may not be able to answer all questions in this survey. Please, verify your browser parameters. \ndefault\n#  Can I use Benchtop NMR in my lab? \n\ud83d\uddd322 June 2026\n\ud83d\udd5b3:00\u20135:00 p.m. CEST \n\ud83d\udcccvia Zoom\n## We are pleased to invite you to our upcoming workshop, **\u201c Can I use Benchtop NMR in my lab?\u201d** taking place on **22 June 2026, from 3:00\u20135:00 p.m. CEST via Zoom**.\nJoin us for an interactive workshop on how **benchtop NMR** can simplify and accelerate routine analytical and QC workflows \u2014 and how **HQSpectrum** can help turn molecular structures into reliable low-field reference spectra.\nBenchtop NMR has strong potential to simplify and accelerate routine analytical workflows. But where does it truly add value, and how can it be implemented effectively?\nThis workshop shows how to turn benchtop NMR data into actionable decisions in everyday lab operations and to obtain reliable results with minimal interpretation effort.\nRather than focusing on theory alone, this practical session will enable you to assess whether benchtop NMR is applicable to your use cases.\nAs part of the session, Merck KGaA, Darmstadt, Germany will present ChemisTwin\u00ae, an online platform for automated NMR spectra interpretation supported by a database of digital Reference Materials (dRMs).\nQ Magnetics will present the QM-125, a 125 MHz benchtop NMR with superb resolution and a flexible platform for walk-up use, automation, and hyphenation.\n**What you will learn**\n1.how to determine if benchtop NMR is a viable and cost-effective solution for their lab\n2.where benchtop NMR adds the most value in routine analysis workflows \n3.how to move from molecular structure to clear, decision-ready spectral insights \n4.practical tools and approaches to simplify spectrum interpretation\n## _**Preliminary Agenda**_\n**1. Welcome & Workflow Framing ****10 min | HQS**\n**2. From Measurement to Interpretation: Closing the Gap****30 min |****Merck + QMagnetics**\n**3. HQSpectrum in the Workflow: When and Why to Use It****25 min | HQS Chemistry Team**\n**4. Hands-On Session: Test Your Molecules****30 min | Interactive Session**\n**5. Discussion: Where This Fits in Your Lab****Optional | 20 min**\n**6. Key Takeaways & Activation | 10 min**\nA detailed agenda will be provided on our webpage and via email.\nThank you for your interest in our upcoming workshop \u2014 we look forward to welcoming you!  \n  \nThis Webinar is hosted by HQS Quantum Simulations.  \nVisit our Webpage to explore more about our Solutions:   \n[www.quantumsimulations.de](https://quantumsimulations.de/)\nThere are 4 questions in this survey. \nBy submitting this registration form, you agree that we may use your personal information for organizational purposes. Please note our information on how we process personal data: <https://quantumsimulations.de/data-protection>\nWe are sorry but you can't proceed without first agreeing to our survey privacy policy. \nI agree \nNext \nLoad unfinished survey\n[Close](https://forms.cloud.quantumsimulations.de/webinar-can-i-use-benchtop-NMR-in-my-lab)\n",
